    "caption": "The world's biggest rodent, and everyone's favourite chill friend.",
    "shortDescription": "Capybaras are the largest rodents on Earth — basically a guinea pig the size of a Labrador — and they are so calm and sociable that birds, monkeys, and even caimans have been photographed sitting on them unbothered. They love water, spend most hot afternoons half-submerged, and can hold their breath for five minutes. Fun fact: Capybaras have slightly webbed feet that make them surprisingly fast swimmers."
